genresAdvancedInfo.name: late romantic era
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Late Romantic Era music is a style of classical music that emerged in the late 19th century and is characterized by lush harmonies, rich orchestration, and an emphasis on emotion and expression. Composers such as Gustav Mahler, Richard Strauss, and Sergei Rachmaninoff are associated with this period.
